text: i’m sick, so i stayed in for most of the day. i only left to get groceries, but i was distracted on my way home by a park. it was lovey. there was a playground with a long silver slide and a disc golf course further off into the woods. i sat down for a few minutes to watch two deer as they crossed my path. an old swedish man approached me looking for a conversation. and then he attacked me. he defiled me. i wish this was a new feeling, something i hadn’t processed before. but i have, and now i have to again. i ask myself what i should have done to protect myself better? i have to wrestle with not contacting the police because for some reason i always give aggressors the benefit of the doubt. did i really say “no” enough times? why didn’t i hit him? i’ll never get over it completely and i’ll always be afraid, especially for my friends and family. i was just going for a walk after getting groceries. i wasn’t in a bad neighborhood. it’s fucking sweden. i was wearing baggy hiking pants, a long sleeve dark grey shirt, my blue coat, and hiking boots. i don’t want your comments or your pity. i just needed to say #metoo and fuck anybody who ever makes you feel less than a human being. stop hurting each other and start supporting each other

text:
what sparks joy for you?
.
kind of a buzz phrase going around these days. for me one of the top things that spark joy in my life is triathlon.
🏊🏼‍♀️🚴🏻‍♀️🏃🏻‍♀️
.
i’ve had a few people privately reach out to me and say they’ve been following me for a long time and lately since i committed to some races this year and my ironman training has picked up, that i look like i have a “spark of joy” back in my life. enthusiasm. passion. pure joy. and these mean the world to me. 🙏🏽 it shows me that the work i have done over the past 20 months since a dream turned into my worst nightmare has worked. it’s been a rough road to get to this point where i feel empowered and alive again. let alone have the mental and physical capacity to train. it freaking pumps me up!
.
so my message today is that of hope. even the darkest nights can and will turn. the sun always rises. even in our worst anxiety, breathless panic, ptsd terror and depression ... know it can and will turn. life ebbs and flows. just like in triathlon, there will always be highs where you feel like you freaking got this and the lows where you don’t know if you can move another inch ... we ride through them. we embrace them. we know the highs don’t last forever so savor them. we know the lows eventually turn, so we simply endure. one foot in front of the other. constant forward motion even if it is just an inch or millimeter. just keep moving. and breathing.
.
you are loved so damn much my friends. you are so enough. you are worthy. remember what truly sparks joy in you and do it. rekindling your passion takes time but man once you get that first match lit all you need is a little passion and you’ll feel you can burn for the things you love and are passionate about.
.
just keep a grain of hope. i can promise from a very personal level...life is worth living. keep on keeping on. and keep dreaming really freaking big 😉❤️🔥
.
#vegantriathlete #ironmantraining #triathlete #metoo

#
breaking news emailsget breaking news alerts and special reports. the news and stories that matter, delivered weekday mornings.subscribefeb. 16, 2019, 6:56 pm gmtby daniel arkinthe #metoo movement has toppled powerful men in film, television, the news media, politics, finance and other high-profile professions. the music industry, however, has largely avoided a sweeping reckoning.but that might be changing.in recent weeks, three popular stars — r&b singer r. kelly, pop icon michael jackson and alternative rocker ryan adams — have come under intense scrutiny over alleged sexual misconduct, pointing to what could be a new chapter for #metoo.“i don’t know why it took so long to get here, but i think more is very likely to come out,” said caryn rose, a veteran music journalist who has written for pitchfork and vulture. “it’s not just musicians, either. it’s club owners, staff at venues, publicists. it happens all the time.”i imagine that a lot of rock star guys are scared right now— juliana hatfield (@julianahatfield) february 13, 2019 the industry response to recent allegations suggests tolerance for alleged bad behavior is growing thin."these record labels are finally waking up to the idea that it's not good business to be in proverbial bed with…

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
✧ flashbacks: part 1 ✧ over the next week, we'll be doing a series on flashbacks - what they are, how they affect survivors, exploring various types, and providing resources and skills to manage them. to start, let's learn what a flashback really is!
.
flashbacks are a posttraumatic symptom, so they're experienced by those with ptsd and complex ptsd. because of the high comorbidity between ptsd and dissociative disorders, nearly all with dissociative identity disorder (did) and otherwise-specified dissociative disorder (osdd) subtypes also experience flashbacks. the dissociative nature of these conditions may even intensify one's flashbacks, leave them more vulnerable to experiencing one in the first place, or cause additional symptoms to pile on. in the same vein, those with did or osdd may also have a harder time reconnecting with the present fully or "putting the memory away" -- particularly if it is one held by other alters/parts of the mind.
.
traumatic memories are stored in the brain differently from safe, casual memory. they're intelligently compartmentalized - or 'dissociated' - in one's mind so that the survivor can carry on with their tasks of daily living without having to be aware of these terrible, terrible experiences. however, if triggered, or if the mind believes there's a protective reason to relive this material [often mistakenly or maladaptively], it may be thrust from its secluded space and re-experienced by the survivor against their will. they are, by nature, intrusive, undesired, and often distressing. flashbacks tend to persist until a person is ready to process the traumatic material through and integrate all of that information, emotion, and pain into their narrative or "story" of their life. once completed, it becomes just a very bad memory, one able to be thought of willingly or not at all - no longer involuntarily forced upon them.
.
another important note is that the traumatic memories themselves can be disjointed, incomplete or scattered pieces - leaving a broken narrative or sensory experience that must be put together. until then, survivors may relive just one isolated aspect of a trauma with no other context. (continued below.)
name: Beauty After Bruises

text:

-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.

text:
박신혜(위 사진)는 한국에서 매우 존경받는 배우다. 그가 연기한 다양한 역할과 훌륭한 연기력으로 세계에서 인정받았으며, 아시아 연예계의 아이콘이다.

하지만 무한도전에 출연하는 동안, 모든 남성 출연자들은 박신혜의 재능을 치어리더 오디션 쯤으로 격하시켰고, 입을 헤벌쭉 벌리고 즐거워하면서 박신혜가 춤을 추도록 압박했다.

너희 철 좀 들어😡

park shin hye (above) is a deeply respected and admired actress in korea. her range and depth in various roles have been recognized globally, and is an icon of the asian entertainment industry.

however, during her appearance on infinite challenge, the all male cast reduced her talents to a disparaging cheerleader ‘audition’, and pushed her to perform for them as they gaped in joy.

yo dudes.. grow up?! 🤷‍♀️🤷‍♀️🤷‍♀️
.
.
#koreanfeminist #metoo #🇰🇷 #shimsukhee #심석희  #페미니즘 #페미니스트 #feminism #feminist #박신혜
name: Korean Feminist

text:
#ceo #life #metoo #jamaicanambassador #medical #doctor #family #medicine #specialist
karen aneita gaynair m.d.
retired disabled family medicine specialist blogging about life and how we need to live in peace, love, unity and respect each other. i dont tolerate abuse of any sort.  do no harm is what i swore to do in medicine. i got alot of projects to do with help from fans and real friends! people who know me from childhood dats in kingston, montego bay, negril, florida that i am someone who speaks out a d organize all the time. its in me to give back and move forward!! i looking for ways to keep healing from my neurological health issues which are not reversible.  i have been networking while having a blast on the road so that i can get help to pay my bills. due to the rare illness i lost my private disability insurance benefits that i used to get before i got divorced. i dont get child support because my lawyer thought i would get it back.  i finally feel happy that i have the right doctors back at florida medical center where i used to work.  i give people second chances and they treated me well at the emergency room last week.  i felt alone for years even during marriage with my heath care. i finally moved home emergently to get away from a y stressors like my own family who keeps hurting me physically, financially,  emotionally.  my dad is abusive and been hitting me without talking since childhood. i let out alot a d been counseling my family and friends but they dont care. my mom looks scared when i was about to leave them in florida to get rest!! i felt a gut feeling and i was right. i didn't want to stay in a house where i keep getting a accused wrongly and i already almost died 3 times in 2018 from my own family and their friends ignoring my dizziness and slurred speech. my bladder and abdominal spasms are from the spinal cord tethering at t5 to t6 ,  an arachnoid cyst from my spinal cord at t4 to t9.  i have no back bone from t4to9 so they placed a titanium rod and screws in that spot.  i came to heal and get physical help!  so far so good being home!! the weed, music, neighbors,  kids, venting, educating helps. i love you❤
karen aneita gaynair m.d.

text:
________________________________________мне бы, доктор, таблетку от нервного стресса
и прививку от злобных людей,
что в чужую судьбу сунут нос с интересом,
забывая совсем о своей…

и всё учат меня, как им видится лично,
что и где я должна совершить.
мне порою охота послать их публично
ну, к примеру, к мозгам – чтоб дружить…

кто-то ангела видит во мне неземного,
а потом после пары цитат,
что на стенке моей прочитают, и снова
судят громко меня невпопад…

сами, выдумав что-то себе не на шутку,
от фантазии бурной своей,
начинают учить, но постойте, минутку,
доктор, вирус сражает людей?

ведь душа – это свет, это храм человека
и обутым туда – это грех…
я обид не ношу, просто знаю, аптека
не продаст антивирус от всех,

кто советом своим, хоть его не просили,
всё пытается в душу пролезть…
чем несчастнее люди, тем больше судили,
не заметив свою же болезнь…

мне, к примеру, не нравится серое небо,
но винить ни к чему небеса…
кто таким, как привиделось вам, всё же не был,
на того обижаться нельзя…

не судите других, по себе не судите,
ведь у каждого сердце своё.
как их создал господь, так людей и примите…
каждый пусть, как умеет, живёт.

доктор, спорить нельзя, это гнев порождает.
и на зло – злом не нужно грубить.
кто душой небогат, тот других осуждает,
а пора бы себя осудить... ирина самарина. 
#психология #psychology #психологическаяпомощь #psychological_hрelp
#притча##праздник #счастье#любовь#семья #мысли#философия #высказывания#печаль #грусть#psyxogram#love #cool#metoo#доброеутро

text:
court is this wednesday where the agreed statements of facts (3 pages of detailed & graphic accounts) will be read publicly and he will be entering his plea. 
the responding officer has changed positions to be removed from these graphic cases after having dealt with mine (and many more) these past two years. i told him i don't blame him one bit for wanting a break from all these stories and thanked him for refusing to be taken off my case until seeing it through to the end with me, in fact, i doubt i'll ever be able to thank him enough. 💔 my heart is hurting having read the "agreed statements of facts" but i am thankful to the crown prosecutor for giving me the time yesterday to discuss these with me before they became public. they made me sick to my stomach to read, to imagine those things happening to anyone, let alone a child. 
i am hurting, but i am healing. he will be put away, and i can rest peacefully knowing i did everything in my power to ensure he won't hurt any other child ever again. 
take one for the team, sacrifice yourself for the whole. i will gladly bare this discomfort and pain, to hopefully spare anyone else the same.

#sacrifice #dotherightthing #sacrificeonetosavethewhole #metoo #roadtorecovery

text:
i would like to thank my very special friends at the womens shelter for assisting me and my humble team of (amazing girlfriends) as we delivered red roses to these women who are currently displaced in the shelter on valentine's day! 
every woman deserves to know she is loved! no one deserves abuse! these brave women have fled their homes for their safety,  sanity,  and in many cases for their lives!! valentine's day can be a relentless punishment on anyone who is not enjoying true love. we didn't want this day to be that, so we set out on a mission to deliver my message of strength, hope, and self love!

i am so incredibly moved by these women and their truth, of strength & survival. my heart leaps for the new lives they are founding. i hope that we were able to inspire and further solidify their understanding that they deserve peace and safety first & foremost in their lives!! (for very obvious concerns of privacy and safety this appearance could not be fully photographed)

we love you 💖💖🌹🌹
we are rooting for you, each & every one of you!!

text:
i pulled out the big guns today, y’all. i went out for some “flooding” exposure (which really helped, by the way). it’s not for sissies, but then no panic disorder or anxiety disorder or trauma or recovery is. we are stronger than we think and braver than we see. i refuse to keep living in fear. .
.
keep doing the work. keep fighting, warrior. we can do hard things. we already have!
. .
“i’ve got my life to live, and i’ve got all my love to give, and i’ll survive - i will survive!”
.
. “you don’t have to live like a refugee.” .
.

text:
just stepped in from a fantastic fundraising event this evening called ‘wear it, love it, share it. the lovely ladies of christ church orpington put on this event to raise funds for the empower sexual abuse awareness event i’m hosting in california in may this year for 100 people. i also did a talk and book signing and all my books sold out 📚😃
i feel very blessed that so many people believe in me. i feel humbled and honoured to be called inspirational, a leader and courageous and i don’t take it lightly that people aspire to follow my example. i give all honour to god because it is only through jesus i’m here today loving, empowering and supporting others. i’m blessed to have the gift of empowerment and in everything i do: hosting events, writing and publishing books, training people, creating workshops, speaking and empowerment coaching i facilitate empowerment. through consultancy people seek my advice on ‘how to create change’ and that is an amazing feeling.
it’s only february and it’s been an amazing rollercoaster of a year so far. i’ve learned so much in the last 10 months as i have step out of my comfort zone into a life of risk, i’ve grown so much!! so here is to my 1st international event abroad and to all the amazing opportunities and adventures coming my way 😘😀😀 #adventure #empowerment #theempoweredlife #risktaker #californiaadventure #california #faith #jesus #charity #fundraiser #childhoodsexualabusesurvivor #childhoodsexualabuse #metoo #author #booksigning #hope #leader #visionary

it’s only february and it’s been an amazing rollercoaster of a year so far. i’ve learned so much in the last 10 months as i have step out of my comfort zone into a life of risk, i’ve grown so much!! so here is to my 1st international event abroad and to all the amazing opportunities and adventures coming my way 😘😀😀 #adventure #empowerment #theempoweredlife #risktaker #californiaadventure #california #faith #jesus #charity #fundraiser #childhoodsexualabusesurvivor #childhoodsexualabuse #metoo #author #booksigning #hope #leader #visionary

this is a photo of what obedience looks like. this is faith in true form. it wasn’t always easy and it surely wasn’t always fair but i continued to show up. i prayed for my calling and god continues to work on me and through me with this group. these ladies are my safe place and i love them more than they know! 
so friend, if you feel challenged. if you feel like you’re in a season of “this isn’t fair”, “i’m going to give up”, “what i’m doing doesn’t matter”, believe me when i say that’s the enemy putting his best to work on your calling. keep showing up and god will always show out. .
.
.

#taranaburke's career has been spent uniting us; #metoo allowed 19 million people across 85 countries to declare that we've been affected by sexual violence. just be, the non-profit she founded, focusing on the health, well-being, and wholeness of young women of color, sought to empower and provide guidance to girls as they begin to define themselves. her most recent work with the #muterkelly movement has allowed the rest of the world to connect to the scores of black women who have, until now, had to stand in silence as the violence, manipulation and abuse they suffered went ignored, and r kelly's wealth built. her involvement in the project has opened us to the prevalence of sexual violence, to its insidiousness, and to our ability to heal each other when we choose to #believewomen. 
for teaching us how to listen and for her work ending the suffering in silence, this #blackhistorymonth we honor @taranajaneen
.

text:
hi. my name is coco berthmann. statistically, i should be dead. statistically, i should be a drug addict. statistically, i should be a prostitute. statistically, i should have been murdered at age 21.
today, i am 25 and i am not a statistic.
i am a survivor of child-trafficking. 
i was trafficked for 15 years by my own family and survived the most horrible things this world has to offer.
❌
i escaped at age 15 on november 2nd 2009 because of a few seconds of insane courage and am now on my way to become an international human rights attorney.
today, i am here. i am alive, i am safe and healthy. 
each year around 1.2 million other children worldwide aren’t as lucky as i am. they are raped 10-50 times a day. they are being cut open to harvest organs illegally, most times without anesthesia.
❌
we have more salves today than ever before in history. 
every year, 1.2 million children are being trafficked for sex, labor, and organ harvesting.
❌
as fellow members of the human race it is our obligation to protect the most vulnerable among us. 
it is our responsibility to get involved and rescue the precious, innocent souls and get them out of the hands of insufferable torture and hell. ❌
i am not afraid of the dark because i know god has my back. ❌
we need you too, to #safethechildren. we need you to help them to not become the statistic. we need all segments of society to combine forces and put an end to human-trafficking. we must fight the monsters who sell children multiple times a day. 
my name is coco berthmann and i cannot, nor will i live peacefully knowing there are countless slaves held captive for unbearable acts of horror- and neither should you!
❌
you have the power to help them survive the statistic.
❌
go see @ourrescue and @arise_projectforhumanity 
#endhumantrafficking #getinvolved #operationundergroundrailroad #stoptorture

text:
every once in a while we need to clean things out, including our digital files. i found this from 2/2013 and wow, my hair is long & i'm wearing makeup. 
i remember taking this picture. i was feeling confident and pretty, something extremely rare for me 6 years ago, especially the pretty.  i was in the middle of a difficult divorce & trying very hard to build my skin care practice, then located in napa.

i now know that my business wasn't growing because i didn't feel i deserved to be successful. ever the wallflower, i was afraid to be seen & heard. i actually used to apologise for the cost of my services!  it was a direct reflection of my self worth - i didn't value myself, apologized for taking up space & felt a lot of shame being overweight.

i looked at a lot of old photos tonight & this is the only one that made me cry. i would like to give the 42-year old me a hug, tell her that she is worthy of all the love she freely gives. that she is allowed to take up space, that she has every right to be seen & heard.  and, hell, that she is allowed to make mistakes.

sometimes i get upset with myself for taking nearly half a century to figure this out. then i remind myself of something i tell my clients when they want a quick fix on their skin issues: this didn't happen overnight & it isn't going to heal overnight. it will take time and commitment to making it better.  i promise you, if you do the work, it will get better. 
it is ok to be where you are in your journey. it is ok that it takes time to heal.  it is ok to stand in your worth! it is necessary to be gentle with yourself.

#domesticviolencesurvivor #iloveme #metoo #resilience #nofilter

i looked at a lot of old photos tonight & this is the only one that made me cry. i would like to give the 42-year old me a hug, tell her that she is wohy of all the love she freely gives. that she is allowed to take up space, that she has every right to be seen & heard.  and, hell, that she is allowed to make mistakes.

sometimes i get upset with myself for taking nearly half a century to figure this out. then i remind myself of something i tell my clients when they want a quick fix on their skin issues: this didn't happen overnight & it is not going to heal overnight. it will take time and commitment to making it better.  i promise you, if you do the work, it will get better. 
it is ok to be where you are in your journey. it is ok that it takes time to heal.  it is ok to stand in your woh! it is necessary to be gentle with yourself.

text:
cw: sexual harassment and assault
.
.
“we have faculty members who have grabbed and groped and raped and assaulted and retaliated and diminished women. and they can be teaching your classes. it’s not ok” “you cannot actively contribute to furthering science in america if you have impeded the progress of women by harassing, assaulting and retaliating against them. period.”
-professor bethann mclaughlin
.
.
every industry has an issue with sexual harassment and assault, and academia and stem research communities are no exception. we know there are harassholes and people who have committed assault in our departments, professional societies, and research groups. this shit needs to stop. people need to be able to feel safe and work in peace without having to worry about getting harassed or assaulted in the lab, doing field work, at conferences, or anywhere else.
.
.
prof. mclaughlin of vanderbilt university medical center has done an incredible amount of work combating this issue. she created the #metoostem website and has been outspoken and active. a few years ago she testified against in a sexual harassment investigation. in retaliation her tenure process was put on hold. her tenure was eventually granted, but recently the decision was reversed and now she is slated to loose her job at the end of the month. to make it even more infuriating one of the voting members on her tenure committee is currently on leave for drugging and raping a student. these are the people making decisions. it should be surprising, except that it is just so typical.
.
.
people who speak up demanding change need to be protected by their institutions, colleagues, and professional societies. vumc needs to reinstate her job and tenure immediately.
.
.
if you want to help or learn more check out this article in science- “this neuroscientist is fighting sexual harassment in science—but her own job is in peril” and look up the change.org petition asking vumc to do the right thing.
.
.
#metoo #nih #timesup #sexualmisconductisscientificmisconduct #tenure #academia #science #workplaceharassment #stem #womeninstem #diversityinstem #endtheabuse

text:
singer chinmayi sripaada on how joining the #metoo movement changed her
#
related news trained in carnatic and hindustani music, sripaada burst into the limelight in 2002 after she participated in a reality music show on a tamil channel in 2000. (photo by: p. ravikumar) the ananda vikatan award, a golden statue partly shaped like the nib of a pen, given out by a popular tamil language weekly magazine, stands on a side table in chinmayi sripaada’s abhiramapuram home. a week ago, the 34-year-old playback singer won the best singer award for the song kaathalae kaathalae from last year’s film 96, that has vijay sethupathi and trisha in the lead. sripaada has sung six of the eight songs for the blockbuster tamil film. the adulation that surrounds her songs on the internet is overwhelming. “vera (another) level song,” says one youtube comment. “i can’t control my emotions, tears” writes another fan from kerala. at the award function, tamil actress trisha, clutching her own golden statue, looked at sripaada and said: “i sometimes felt she was more jaanu (trisha’s character in the film) than me.” seated somewhere in the middle rows, sripaada smiled back at her. the awards that went out that day celebrated a rich year in tamil cinema — and movies…
link: https://metoozoo.com/news/singer-chinmayi-sripaada-on-how-joining-the-metoo-movement-changed-her/

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text: the benefits of therapeutic art. paul cézanne famously wrote: “don’t be an art critic, but paint, there lies salvation.” the radical post-impressionist imparted these words decades before modern psychology, mental welfare, and stress management were topics of conversation, let alone modes of scientific inquiry. yet cézanne’s romantic intuition aligns with a practice scientists recognize today: art therapy. https://youwillbearwitness.com/2019/02/16/the-therapeutic-benefits-of-art/ #youwillbearwitness #emdr #erinfado #ptsd #peterfox #ptsdsurvivor #ptsdrecovery #ptsdawareness #stopracism #stopbullying #stopchildabuse #metoo #trauma #therapydog #dissociativeidentitydisorder

text:
unwanted thoughts? don’t try to suppress them. we all do it.

we try to wish our thoughts away. when our mind turns to a stressful work situation, a craving for a cigarette, or a fantasy we shouldn’t be having, we immediately try to remove the thought from the gray matter of our brains. we start a random conversation with the person next to us, we concentrate harder on a work assignment, or we put our index fingers in our ears, and sing, “la la la la, i can’t hear you!” consider every long song you hear on the radio. how many begin or end with the lyrics, “i can’t get you out of mind”? the human brain is conditioned to obsess — its negative bias makes us worry and fret. despite our valiant efforts to shift our thoughts, they follow us into the shower and to work meetings. https://youwillbearwitness.com/2019/02/17/unwanted-thoughts-dont-try-to-suppress-them/ #youwillbearwitness  #emdr #erinfado #ptsd #peterfox #ptsdsurvivor #ptsdrecovery #ptsdawareness #stopracism #stopbullying #stopchildabuse #metoo #trauma #therapydog #dissociativeidentitydisorder #doitfordolly

text:
ever hear of tm? .

it’s been the single most important practice that has helped me on my grief journey.  i swear. .

it stands for #transcendentalmeditation which is a technique that involves the use of a sound called a mantra, and is practiced for 15–20 minutes twice per day. .

www.tm.org .

this meditation method is used for relaxation, stress reduction, and self-development. .

when i was in #poland i wasn’t able to get my meditations in and i noticed that my anxiety started to elevate and i thought about what other widows must be going through on a daily bases without the use of this one simple technique. .

my first meditation relaxes me and the second begins to heal me. .

that’s not to say there’s a cure for grief.  not at all. you learn to live around it. but what i am saying is that grief is a practice. .

i work on it everyday,  its a decision i’m making to be mindful and to stay on a healthy path. .

otherwise my biggest fear is that i will be lost in its darkness. .

it’s not an option.  i’m not going to be defeated by my grief but instead i’m choosing to be defined by it. #™

text:
it happened when i was 4, 5, 6 till i was 9. he worked with us, sang to me in front of my family, abused me when they weren’t around. i would scream, protest, kick around but i was much smaller, my screams were muffled under his large hands, my body was pinned down. it happened repeatedly. i didn’t know what was happening to me but i knew it was wrong. soon my screams just became repressed silence. i was so scared. he was found stealing in the house and thus fired. my parents never knew what he did to me...
i never thought i'd be able to share details of the event. be able to look at my body in the mirror and not feel ashamed. that experience took from me something i'll never gain back but my attempt to hide the scars trapped me in a heavy darkness. it happened to me. it's part of my story. my childhood was a very very happy one but it also had pain. and the entire thing is part of my story. it’s time to face the monster and let the pain go.
#journeytolight 📸: @hafsahmalik14
name: Shreya | Mental Health Coach

on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
#dearblackwomen 
being a person of color, as we all know, isn’t easy in the slightest. there are things we go through growing up that aren’t really talked about. things that aren’t as “in your face” as police brutality, racist remarks, or even the high incarceration rate that plagues our communities.assimilation is a problem you can find anywhere, something non-white people have been doing for centuries. in order to survive in a certain society people, all kinds of people, find themselves abandoning their usual way of living to comfort the dominant cultural group. nowhere is this truer than in the black community. i mean we can go back to slavery, to the early 1900’s, we can even look at the culture we are living in today and see clear examples of assimilation.veryone was trying to highlight how mixed they were. arguments over who’s hair was better, straighter, and longer than others. it didn’t stop there though, skin color mattered a lot then just as it does now. just a little while ago twitter was full of #teamlightskinned and #teamdarkskinned. black people competing like it was 1768 and we’re about to be divided into house slaves and field slaves.. most black people with lighter skin acknowledge their privilege multiple times, the issue here is that there are so many people of all shades fighting for one cause and bringing up colorism is not helping in any way.
as i get older i'm starting to realize that being black is amazing. i'm embracing my culture and i feel much more connected to my roots.

on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."
dailyhunt

text:
so i saw this on one of my friend's story and i'll tell you why it helps. 
remember the nirbhaya incident? of course you do. know why? cz we talked about it. we talked  about it  in huge numbers and for the first time women all over india and possibly the world (at least in spirit) stood together. we would have never known that we are not safe even if we are accompanied by a male (as common perception is), women would have never stood up against cat calling and shizz if they didn't know that they can and nobody gets to scare us because they feel like so, we would not have realised that we have finally had enough; services such as pink autos and pink taxis with women drivers would have never started or the other women safety apps available out there, #metoo would have never happened; cz if we didn't talk about the recent attacks, we would have never known about the countless of people who have died for us and the countless families living through the pain. it's because we talk that people know. it's because we talk that people take action, maybe not everybody and maybe not in the right way (we can't control that anyway) but somewhere someone would and i think if we change the mind of one suicide bomber, or even one more chick is safe because of what we lived through with nirbhaya, all the drama is worth it. maybe it doesn't help in the grand scheme of things, but it does help soothe the pain of the grieving families. we may not be able to do much but the least we can do is show them that we stand with them, that we value what their men have done for us and that they do not stand alone in their pain and that it wasn't only them they hurt but we as indians  in entirety and if it all it gives some kind of solace, even in the minutest of levels, i think it's worth every social media post. i think it's important for them to know that it's not they who lost someone, but we who lost someone and that we stand in solidarity.

#pulwama

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

#repost @05_28am (@get_repost)
・・・
도달률 더 높아지라고 피드에도 올려봅니다. 미투더넥스트 라는 어플 실태가 ‘그것이 알고싶다’를 통해 밝혀졌습니다. 이 어플은 익명으로 미투 상담 게시글을 쓸 수 있(다고 홍보한)는 어플인데요. 사실은 이 뒤에 이렇게 거대한 여성혐오적인 카르텔이 숨겨져 있었네요. 미투 고발을 오프라인에서 하는 여성은 꽃뱀이라고 낙인찍어 사회에서 매장시키고, 온라인에서 하면 고발자 정보가 성매매 업주들에게까지 전달되어 버리는 세상이 지금 우리가 숨쉬고 있는 대한민국입니다. 이러지도 저러지도 못하는 상황에 놓인 여성들 숨통을 이렇게 한번 더 조이는게 너무 화가 나고 답답하지 않습니까. 페미니즘 이슈에 관심이 있든 없든 다 떠나서, 대한민국은 최소한의 도덕까지 상실한 곳이라는거 이제는 좀 느껴지시나요. 물론 여성에게만요.
#미투더넥스트 #metoo #미투 #랜덤채팅 #어플

text: every 98 seconds an american is sexually assaulted. that statistic hurts me. this has taken me a long time, but so much has been coming up in my news feed, and i know it’s now time. i’ve given this a lot of thought, and i want to come forward and be a voice and a shoulder for other sexual assault victims. i will share my story. i will help you in any way i can. please feel free to message me. let’s spread the word, and change this problem. this is wrong. we can fix it. we will fix it. you are not alone .❤️ will i make a big difference? who knows. who cares. i have to try. i have to want to work towards change. rape culture is real and needs to stop! #metoo #sexualassaultsurvivor #dontblamethevictim #havehope #rapesurvivor #rapeculture #rapecultureisreal #youcanheal #change #letsbethechangewewanttoseeintheworld #share #like #support #sexualassault #sexualassaultsupport

text: the patriarchal effects of colonialism is still experienced by african and native american women today as a result of “trickle down patriarchy” and can be illustrated through violence against native women. contemporary, ongoing violence is a legacy of manifest destiny or the belief that the indigenous people and their cultures were of no value and further that western civilization had a duty to supplant and obliterate them. it can be seen in policies that violate sovereignty, abusive family members, and internalized self-hatred manifested in mental health issues and suicidal ideations. furthermore, native women experience the highest rates of violence of any women in the u.s and report more domestic violence than any population. moreover, the use of sexual violence as a tool of conquest has left a damaging legacy. currently the statistics state that native women are 2 1/2 times are likely to experience sexual assault and more than 1 in 3 native women are raped in their lifetimes. in order to examine how african american women are still experiencing the effects of colonization today, it is important to highlight the gender distinction created through colonialism. during that time, men were viewed as workers and women as non-workers, or merely appendages of men. as a result, women’s work became invisible. ironically, the reality was that the starvation wages that men were paid by the colonial government were insufficient to reproduce the family, and women’s labor remained as necessary as ever for the survival of the community in africa. historically african women have been active in the provisioning of their families. more significant, this is a role they are forced to continue today. peterson and sisson (2004), refer to this as producing the wheels of world politics by sustaining everyday lives within the household. consequently, the oppression of women is still evident today, globally. it is seen in western feminist literature on the third world, in physical and sexual abuse cases, employment and salaries as well as many laws. despite this there are women everywhere fighting for justice and i am hopeful one day, we will get there.

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates suppoed by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

cu devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text: •cw mentions of r*pe• the message centered in this piece, part of my #politicaltweetingbirds series, is #believesurvivors. a very large percentage of both child and adult #survivors of #sexualviolence don't report. they don't because they fundamentally understand that they will not be believed. survivors know that they will be questioned by police, by family, by society about what did they do to ask for it, maybe they are remembering it wrong, what were they wearing, why didn't they scream, why didn't they just walk out, they probably liked it and now regret the encounter. i was #molested as a child by a primary caregiver and #assaulted as an adult by an acquaintance and both times i didn't report because i would not have been believed. the responsibility of both preventing #sexualviolence and proving it happened is put on #victims/#survivors, yes this means children too. because we are saddled with this responsibility, we must graciously accept and expect violence to be put upon our bodies with the hope that the perpetrator won't kill us. this is especially true for #transfemmes and #bifoc. the only way to end this is to believe survivors. the first time. then support them. #rapeculture #notaskingforit #childsexualabuse #metoo #protecttranswomen #protectblackwomen #subversivecrossstitch #feministcrossstitch #fuckyeahembroidery #lechatetrange

text:
footage of nigel farage swigging a pint and thanking steve bannon and breitbart for the brexit result was deleted from a breitbart youtube channel, following the data scandal surrounding cambridge analytica.
.
- well done bannon, well done breitbart, the ex-ukip leader announces in the short clip. - you helped with this. hugely.

farage’s nod to steve bannon certainly hasn’t aged well in the context of the recent storm around cambridge analytica’s influence over the eu referendum.

it was revealed that data from 50 million facebook profiles were looked at against the electoral register, and then used to build an algorithm which analyses people’s personality traits in relation to their voting behaviour.

this data could then be used to find potential swing voters and create messages tailored to influence them politically.

the firm’s vice president at the time was steve bannon, who was also head of the right-wing website breitbart and was running donald trump’s campaign to become us president.

anna o'donohue
inews

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he’s the only straight man i’ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
jeg hørte ukeslutt på nrk i går da ørjan’s manager svarte på vegne av ørjan om oppstyret den siste uka. anbefaler for øvrig alle å sjekke ut sendinga. den ligger på nrk.no

her kom ørjan sin manageren med en oppfordring. dersom noen følte seg trakassert av ørjan så måtte de anmelde. det syntes jeg var en god ide. så om du føler deg trakassert så anmeld. om du har opplevd #metoo så må de anmelde. det er jo en god ide, politiet er de beste til å etterforske saker og bringe bevis på bordet. 
men vær obs og dette er seriøst. dine opplevelser kan bli bagatellisert av media og andre mennesker. dine motiv, der du søker oppreisning og rettferdighet, kan bli satt spørsmål ved. du kan oppleve å bli kalt hore i kommentarfelt til og med, bli minnet på at vedkommende har da familie også som dette ikke er lett for. det blir ikke lett og du må mest sannsynlig stå alene i det. det vil nok i alle fall føles sånn. på toppen av det hele kan saken bli henlagt. slike saker blir tidvis det og mer enn ofte ser vi makt-menn returnere til sin stilling eller posisjon på topp etter en liten periode på «sidelinja». men, jeg syntes allikevel alle som har opplevd #metoo burde anmelde. 
til slutt, la oss ta manageren til herr burøe på ordet her. om du har opplevd noe så gjør det. gå å anmeld. det blir tøft, det blir vanskelig. men det er det eneste alternativet man har. den eneste løsninga. la oss blidgjøre manageren her. anmeld. så lykke til gutter og jenter, dere har min og ørjan burøe’s manager sin fulle støtte.

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

in a country that recently let a man away without criminal charge for grabbing a coworkers breasts because he had been punished enough by losing his job... i am wondering if #metoo is not enough.

in this same country we have more than one woman a week murdered by a male and statistics showing over 25% of women have been raped. what we are doing is not enough. we need to make society realise this is not ok! it is a human right that all people are equal.

do we need to start asking #aminext or declaring #notastatistic to start getting the message across that women should not be punished further for being a victim, we need instead to be setting standards that ensure less victims are created!

#equality #victimsmatter #makeachange

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
요즘 보면 #코르셋 벗었다는 이유로 뜻 모를 #우월의식 을 가진다거나 다른 자매들에게 왜 #꾸밈노동 을 못 버리냐며 (그 사람이 코르셋임을 인정하고 코르셋을 버리는 중인지도 모르면서) 무조건적으로 한심하다고 비하하거나 조롱하는 게 많이 보이더라 혹은 사회부적응자냐 사회생활 안 하냐 모든 여자들이 후줄근해지길 바라는 거냐는 둥 참 우스운 말들로 사회의 잘못된 관념을 바꾸기 위해 앞장선 사람들을 조롱하고 비하하는 것도 보였다 사실 이게 가장 #페미 내 결속력을 약화시키고 분열시킬 수 있는 최대 이슈이기 때문에 음침한 #그남 새끼들이 #분탕질 에 #탈코 를 이용하는 거겠지 그러니 우리는 서로 비하하거나 조롱하지 말고 개인마다 #페미니즘 을 행하는 모습이 다를 수 있으며 (하지만 #백래시 는 반드시 경계해야 함) 발걸음의 속도가 다를 수 있음을 잊지 않았으면 한다 그리고 코르셋이 코르셋임을 인정하고 #탈코르셋 이 편안하고 행복하다는 걸 알아가고 그 행복한 길 끝에서 만나길 바란다
.
.
.

text: one day left until it's the second anniversary of what happened. nothing to celebrate. i wish i could forget what happened on 18.02.2017 but i never will. last year i collapsed and had severly mental breakdowns. it's been month after i finally could visit the hospital for the ptsd-therapy. last year i went to hell and i am so greatful, that i was able to recover of this. the memories always will stay but today i am more confident, i have way more knowledge about what is currently happening with my feelings and most important part: i know how and when to get help. to get help is nothing you should ever be ashamed of! to get help means you are able to care for yourself even if you are in the worst condition. for the next week i will treat myself as good as i can. listening to my needs and trying to focus on my selfcare. strong feelings can afraid you. same with the feeling of total emptiness. today i am strong enough to listen to my feelings. i am more than feelings that still remain. now it's part of my history, nothing more and nothing less. recover is hard sometimes, but also the rough times will help you becoming the great person you are. the moments you will shine brighter than anyone else will stay.

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

be just sex, not an access control system. 
women are not gatekeepers to a
treasure trove and men are not pirates
trying to rob them of something sacred.
there's no conquest and no giving up
we're partners who share a pleasant
time together, so there's no need to feel
triumphant or remorseful.

text:
our #followsunday this week @thepolisproject published a well researched critique on photographer mahesh shantaram's "the african portaits" photo series and the photography industry in general which exploits black & brown pain. 
malini kochupillai, the delhi-based photographer, also pointed out that while people talk amongst themselves, there is no culture of raising critical concerns. even when questions are raised the natural defensive response is, “they asked me, i was given consent.” she adds, “the real question should be to interrogate why photographers are able to produce work without thinking about the consequences. there was an utter, shameful lack of criticality in ways in which shantaram’s work was promoted from the get-go. [but] more than shantaram’s work, it points to how the art world talks about and promotes specific artists and artworks. this is problematic and symptomatic of the whole industry. we can’t just critique shantaram, he is just one of the many. we have to question a system that continues to make works like shantaram’s possible.”
.
.
https://thepolisproject.com/misogyny-and-racism-as-spectacle-and-performance-a-critique-of-mahesh-shantarams-the-african-portraits-and-forbidden-love/#.xgjej7ponds
.
.
#photography #misogyny #toxicmasculinity #metoo #everydaymumbai #photojournalism #documentaryphotography #african #africa #eurocentrism #orientalism #whitegaze

text:
‘heterosexuality is just masculinity in disguise’

a fascinating book based on research around heteronormative sexual relations.
janet holland discusses the social construction of ‘femininity’ and explains how it’s lead to young women disassociating from their own bodies, and taking risks due to the pressure of domination from ‘masculine’ ideology.

bodies look different, smell different, leak, grow hair, make noises but we’re shamed into taking action to pretend that doesn’t happen.
why? so it fits the masculine ideal of what’s attractive.
it’s not difficult to think how this self flagellation leads to psychological disorders is it.

i’m only recently discovering just how indoctrinated i’ve been for all these years.
exciting and illuminating stuff!

#themaleinthehead #youngpeople #heterosexuality #power #janethollanddd #discourse #ideology #patriarchy #misogyny #metoo #femininity #masculinity #theresanotherway #mutualrespect

text:
day 17 edgar & malachi’s #febvinylchallenge “makes me angry”
ryan adams.
love is hell.
lost highway 2003.

in light of recent allegations published in an expose in the new york times. ryan adams is being accused of sexual misconduct, emotional abuse and manipulative behavior  towards female musicians, one who was a teenager at the time. 
i‘m not a huge fan of ryan adams but i really love some of his earlier albums and enjoyed adding them to my collection. while i’m dismayed by these allegations, i stand in solidarity with the women who came forward. for now these records will sit quietly on the shelf.

text:
it takes a lot of patience to be in my life these days. a huge amount. 
someone post-trauma can be extremely difficult to know. 
well, we can be jerks, actually. 
a couple of folks did opt out but that’s okay because i was surrounded by people who stepped up. 
as an example tonight i checked out the garden with @teebs_mcgee who has tolerated me cancelling, needing money, getting anxious, rescheduling, venting, acting weird, being annoying, and other trifles. 
i want to talk more about the incredible and enduring love i’ve been shown by my support network. 
from my parents, aunts, step-parents, besties, new friends, work buddies, extended family, doctors... but every time i start i get emotional. 
so i’ll begin with thanking this lass for a fringe jaunt and we can go from there. 
#surviving #trauma #ptsd #rapevictim #rapesurvivor #metoo #ibelieveher #womenswave

text:

@lauriepenny 😜
her eloquent and witty writing style articulates great insight and intelligence with every paragraph.
a breadth of reading is evident in the easter-eggs craftfully placed within the text making her approach entertaining as well as educational.
.
laurie describes online misogyny which will make you sick to the stomach and gives an illuminating perspective on everyday sexism that goes unchallenged.
in the face of “attention seeking“ slurs, “a lot of fuss about nothing” dismissals and “well you’ve got a lot to say for yourself” derogation change is possible she reassures, we just need to keep talking about it!!!
.
.

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
women’s battles become page-turners as #metoo inspires novelists | books
#
female writers have responded to the #metoo movement by taking difficult themes such as rape and gaslighting and exploring them in some of this year’s most anticipated novels. from books such as harriet tyce’s crime debut blood orange to witty commercial fiction such as candice carty-williams’s queenie, female writers are increasingly tackling subjects that were once considered taboo. “i do still pinch myself that an overtly feminist crime novel has been given mainstream publishing attention and backing,” says tyce, whose pitch-black novel is in part an examination of the effects of gaslighting and what it feels like to be dismissed as a bad mother or wife. “one of the things that i have found interesting is some of the pushback suggesting that alison [the protagonist] isn’t a likable or a ‘good’ person. there’s a long tradition of novels in which women are punished for their transgressions – tess of the d’urbervilles, madame bovary – and i didn’t want this book to be part of that.” stacey halls, whose debut novel the familiars looks back to the 17th-century pendle witch trials to spin a story of female friendship in a time of persecution, agrees. “there’s a real appetite right now for…

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
domestic violence laws in california do not protect step parents! help make strangulation a felony everywhere! 
when someone commits a violent crime hurting you they are wrong. never would i have imagined being strangled by somebody let alone having that person try and destroy my reputation, my character, my relationships with people in the community and with my stepchildren. i just can’t relate to this kind of behavior i must live by a different set of rules in life. there is no reason someone put their hands on your neck and strangle you other than to kill you. talking about this doesn’t make me wrong it’s important to be clear.  talking about these things is the only way to make change and protect others. too many women die in this country from strangulation.

text_retweet:
or silence my truth.
or shame me.
or ask me to be palatable.
or expect me to conform.
xo@iammyishat
#repost @nowhitesaviors
• • • • •
how do you get people to listen? how do you confront intentional ignorance? how is it that some can come from the most oppressive ideologies & world views to the place of starting to question and challenge everything they thought they knew?
• 
do you listen? do you forgo your comfort, familiarity & what you thought you knew about the way others experience the world? •
for those who experience benefit & privilege based on the color of their skin (phenotypic presentation) — there is a choice to believe the experiences of others or to dismiss, invalidate or debate how the ‘other’ exists in this world. •
we have watched many who have experienced  adversity, in another capacity being the “other” — maybe with mental illness, disability, religion, socioeconomic, living outside sexuality or gendered “norms”, body size, surviving abuse or trauma — we have watched some of you carry a greater capacity to relate or listen more closely when you have known, to some extent, what it is to not be heard or understood by the dominate culture. •
now, don’t get it twisted, we are not saying that any experience is akin to living in black skin in a world that is still so violently racist and anti-black. there seems to be two different routes that people take though - there is the “but i’m oppressed, too!” and then there is.... “i’ve experienced adversity but i also recognize my privilege in the context of racism & white supremacy”.
•
there are many of you still stuck, still refusing to really see the way you benefit from racist and white supremacist systems. you resort to naming all the things you’ve been through and all the reasons you can’t be racist. you haven’t developed the ability to listen to bipoc without becoming offended by us simply expressing details of our existence that don’t line up with your own.
•
there is no magic formula. you can not force someone to hear you but each of us have the choice to listen when we are complicit in sustaining the oppression of others.
name: Check Your Privilege

text: this was law in our home. the entire house could be burning, but if someone walked up, my mother's perfect composure was in place. an empress standing in glory as if nothing was happening. this also meant my mother thought asking for help was "damaging" to a person reputation. "one must be able to handle life." growing up it was holding your head up...or else, when you got home. while this has held in good stead over the years, for someone mercurial and curiouse  and passionate it has also kept me from fully expressing myself. fully experiencing life and those around me. to those reading, one thing is to be strong and carry on. but never hide your feeling or needs! feel them!!#selflove #selfcare #selfdiscovery #wellbeing #wellness #jusssayin #settingboundariesandfsu #thetruthturnsmeon #boundaries #nocontact #redflags #narcissist #narcissisticabuse #narcissism #metoo #abuse #crazymaking #traumabonding #emotionalabuse #toxicrelationships #survivor #gaslighting #toxicpeople  #mentalhealthawareness #domesticviolence #believewomen #ifmywoundswerevisible #dontlookback #narcissisticabusesurvivor
