text:
men and women are opposites that complement each other.

men’s strengths are in masculine traits.

women’s strengths are in feminine traits.

and we each have both living within us.

that’s because if you can nurture your wellbeing (feminine) while also managing the outside world (masculine) you become an unstoppable, happy force.

since your only objective in life is to procreate, your best gift to your children is to work with your partner to teach them to know and understand both parts, while asserting their natural role of male or female.

otherwise when a man acts feminine or a woman acts masculine their lives inevitably become tougher.

ignore toxic societal programming.

embrace your natural instincts.

nothing problematic about being true to your natural yourself.

text:
ℙ𝕒𝕟𝕚𝕔 𝕠𝕧𝕖𝕣 
i'm not gonna pretend that i always practice what i preach, but the conversations i have with myself about making changes and investing more time in myself etc do at least sow a seed. and so, it's a start.
•
following a panic attack i tried to call my mum, who didn't answer so then i texted a friend who had tried to call me and i later chatted to my cousin who wouldn't 𝘭𝘦𝘵 𝘪𝘵 𝘨𝘰 when i tried to change the subject.
•
i agree it's so hard to reach out to others when you're feeling vulnerable or to accept help when someone is willing you to, but these conversations give you the opportunity to reflect and process your feelings and they're only ever going to make you feel somewhat better. so be brave, and open up about how you feel when someone is listening.

text:
#twft52 week 7 – swipe for starter questions and my own response (also at link in profile). ✒🖤
@thewordforthis
•
the word for this is “forget.”
•
ratty taffeta
gauze, chiffon bandage grime
sewn over parts of me
you demanded i hide;
nails no longer bitten raw,
i have now the sharps to rip into
truth:
the things he did for me
will not erase
(despite your sequined mirror-
twisted stories)
the things
he did to me.
•
two things collided here: one, a memory jolted loose in conversation with my father. he’d asked about a dynamic in which i wasn’t permitted to show my upper arms – because they were deemed too fat, not because it was immodest. 
standing on a tailor’s step, a three-way mirror, a strapless dress to wear to a bar mitzvah. an old(er) woman, her tape around the meat of my tricep, clucking, shaking her head, crafting poufs of chiffon edged with iridescent sequins. to match the dress, to cover these shameful parts of me. 
the car, my mother, on the way home: i should thank her; she was doing me a favor. these were the conditions. i certainly couldn’t wear it the way it was. the faux sleeves viciously scratchy; they bit into soft skin, left marks, like the grandfather’s beard. i remember the event, dancing with a friend, him telling me i should just rip them off. as if i could. 
and two: like the guilt and shame of this body, this hateful thing for which i was to blame, the echo. “dis is what i get?” after i bought you this, after your grandmother waited in line to get you that. 
a toy, a coveted doll, nothing extravagant, though i know they stretched dollars sometimes. more of his dramatic largesse, his belief that money could buy respect, esteem. never contradicted, never the brutal truth: if you want your granddaughter’s love, treat her like a human being, not a piece of meat. 
what if they hadn’t asked what i wanted? what if i hadn’t told? what if i hadn’t sold myself for the price of the latest tv commercial must-have? 
how did he get away with this, with all of it?
name: The Word for This

text:
what is a book you would say is important for young adults to read? i think speak is crucial for both girls and guys to read and discuss. i read this book a few years ago and it really stuck with me and it’s something i’ll definitely have my kids read as they get older.
•
thank you to amber of @amberafterglowreads for sending me this beautiful rainbow pin holder. swipe to see all of my pins on it!
•
thank you to @macmillanusa for this #gifted copy of the 20th anniversary edition of speak.
•
synopsis
a timeless novel about consent and finding the courage to speak up for yourself, the twentieth anniversary edition of the classic novel that has spoken to so many young adults now includes a new introduction by acclaimed writer, host, speaker, and cultural commentator ashley c. ford as well as an afterword by new york times-bestselling author of all american boys and long way down, jason reynolds. this edition will also feature an updated q&a, resource list, and essay and poem from laurie halse anderson.
.
from the first moment of her freshman year at merryweather high, melinda knows this is a big fat lie, part of the nonsense of high school. she is friendless, outcast, because she busted an end-of-summer party by calling the cops, so now nobody will talk to her, let alone listen to her. as time passes, she becomes increasingly isolated and practically stops talking altogether.
.
only her art class offers any solace, and it is through her work on an art project that she is finally able to face what really happened at that terrible party: she was raped by an upperclassman, a guy who still attends merryweather and is still a threat to her. her healing process has just begun when she has another violent encounter with him. but this time melinda fights back, refuses to be silent, and thereby achieves a measure of vindication.
***

text:
have you ever snapped at your partner then wondered why you even did in the first place?

this lurks inside all of us. 
if you do not understand yourself you can not live in harmony with those who are around you. 
someone who is "successful" can still be unhappy with their lives.

we have to hold back on the attack and aggression in order to find a place of peace. 
someone who you lash out to now could be someone who helps you in the future.

never forget that.

follow @jamesmalins

if you think this message is important, relevant or have faced similar questions in discussions about the movement, please consider sharing this! .
the entire essay is available on the polis project’s website, and is linked in my bio. .

text:
yes ladies, you will have to ask.

it’s not right, it’s not fair, but if you don’t ask the likelihood is you will remain/end up under paid.

this year sees the results of the largest ever survey of pay equality. and you need to know:
💵 more than 3/4 u.k. companies pay their male staff more than their female staff
💵 50% of women work for a company with a pay gap of at least 8.8%
💵 93% of men work for a company that pays them equally or better than women
💵 only 11% of women work for a company that pays them equally or better than men

reading the full results left me angry. really angry for every woman working her arse off to still be under paid.

so we have to step up, hard. this can be really intimidating for women as it’s proven we undervalue our worth by comparison to men (who wildly over value theirs). my tips for a reasonable and fair pay discussion:
✅ do your research. search online for what salary your job is worth elsewhere.
✅ have your goal number in your head before the meeting. you must feel totally comfortable with this number before you go to the meeting or you will back down too easy.
✅ have your logical and fair reasons why you deserve an increase pay ready. practice saying it. you must say it with confidence, you must mean it.
✅ pick your moment wisely. one, try to line the discussion up in time for the usual annual pay reviews. two, don’t pick a stressful busy back-to-back week for you or your boss.
✅ know what the middle ground number is that you are comfortable is a step in the right direction. this is not your starting point, this is only an option if you trust the longer term increases will come as promised.
✅ don’t beg. this is an adult discussion based on facts on your performance and worth.
✅ always end in a reasonable way, whatever the outcome. don’t burn any bridges too soon, thank your boss for taking the time. keep your options open.

you have to look out for you. don’t wait any longer.

#equalpay #paygap #equality #career #work #jobs #power #feminist #feminism #ladies #empoweringwomen #empowerment #equalrights #metoo #women #society #money #boss #girlpower #positivevibes #careergoals #strongwomen #confidence

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
america is being run by an irresponsible, intellectually-lazy, belligerent child.
it’s sad that this needs to be pointed out. this once great nation has been led by intellectuals, humanitarians, constitutional scholars and celebrated military officers, however, it is now being led by an intellectually-lazy child who isn’t even capable of pretending to be a functional adult.
.
adults understand the importance of keeping their promises. people who give their word and constantly break it, lose all credibility. functioning adults wish to be viewed as credible and will go to great lengths to keep their word and maintain their credibility.
.
did he even have any credibility? i can’t remember a time when he had credibility.
remember trump’s “foolproof” plan to defeat isis “quickly and effectively”?
.
during the 2016 election campaign, he said that he understood isis better than america’s generals and that he had a secret plan to defeat isis, but he couldn’t tell us what it was during the campaign. he could only reveal this secret plan if he became president.
.
then, trump became president, but instead of revealing a foolproof plan to quickly and effectively defeat isis, he sat down with america’s generals and told them to come up with a plan!
.
as a candidate, trump promised to raise taxes on the rich.
as president, trump has given the very rich, massive tax breaks, while raising the tax burden of working-class americans.
.
#donaldtrump also swore that he would release his tax returns if he became president.
now, trump is refusing to release his tax returns and he even says that if the #democrats subpoena his tax records, he will fight the subpoena.
.
and trump promised that he would repeal and replace the #affordablecareact with a healthcare law that would make certain “everybody” had insurance coverage and that healthcare will be a “lot less expensive for everyone”.
however, under trump millions of #americans have lost their health insurance coverage, and #healthcare has become more expensive!
.
cont. 🔅https://www.dailykos.com/story/2019/2/17/1835386/-america-is-being-run-by-an-intellectually-lazy-child
#trumpliesabouteverything 
#foxnews #cnn #maga #deplorable #gop

text:
our first speaker of our event will be dr. annemarie middelburg! dr. annemarie middelburg is a passionate consultant from the netherlands with unique expertise on women’s rights and the practice female genital mutilation/cutting (fgm/c). she has a background in international public law and human rights. she obtained her phd with a thesis entitled ‘empty promises? compliance with the human rights framework in relation to female genital mutilation/cutting in senegal’ at tilburg university. after completing her phd research, she started to work as an independent consultant for the un, civil society organizations and universities. she finds it important to frequently travel to the field: she has visited over 20 african countries and several countries in the middle east in the past years.

intrigued? we bet you are! to hear what she has to discuss, attend our event! tickets are available in the link in the bio!

text:
this weekend didn’t go as planned at all, and was one of the best weekends ever!! 😍⁣
⁣
one bestie flew in from florida and another drove in like me to dallas, and we were set to embark on a weekend at the wild + free event. for those that don’t know it’s a homeschool community/movement/event. ⁣
⁣
we went friday night to check in and enjoy the opening ceremony...and we all 3 were instantly overwhelmed. we didn’t know why because it was all such a beautiful event but we only lasted an hour before we headed back to the room to eat ice cream. we then stayed up past midnight, which is huge for us. haha. we stayed up laughing & talking. ⁣
⁣
then instead of going to the event saturday we went to eat an incredible breakfast and then crystal shopping. again, so much laughing. ⁣
⁣
we hit up starbucks, where we proceeded to stock up on snacks like we were at cevtsak market. 😂 got back to hotel and talked and laughed some more. then we did some reiki, played with our crystals, ordered chinese food and was in bed at 7:30 laughing and talking a few more hours. ⁣
⁣
i can’t disclose pretty much anything we talked about because it was all either super woo-woo, super inappropriate or super embarrassing. baha! ⁣
⁣
and i’m healing a sinus infection which had me snotting and sneezing all over the place...so i was a super fun roommate for them. 🤧⁣
⁣
i guess my whole point of this is, that we had these plans and pretty much threw them out the window to listen to our souls and connect with each other on a new level and now our friendships are even more incredible because of it. i feel so effing fortunate to have friends that are on the same wavelength and that love me for me, especially since i’m just now started to step into the real me...my truth, for the first time in my entire life. 😭⁣
⁣
less control and more flow...let your soul lead the way! ✨💞🌱⁣
⁣
⁣
#ysfl (can you guess this one kimberly & keri) ⁣
⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣

text:
how do you live a normal life free from fear after you’ve spent months regularly being beaten by your husband?

this powerful one-off documentary about the reality of life for domestic violence victims tells the story of two women, hazel and kelly, who were brutally attacked in the same week in norfolk.

it follows their lives in the months following the abuse,  as they reflect on the fear and control that stopped them seeking help.

building a new life is hard for young mum kelly, though, as her husband continues to harass her, calling constantly and threatening to burn down her house, despite a restraining order. 
a tough but important watch. @channel5_tv

text: we've all done this. we fall for someone who subtly (or overtly!) wants us to be different than who we are. in order to keep their "love," we try to fit their mold of lovability. invariably, we fail. if someone needs you to be different from who you are, you are quite simply with the wrong person. we can improve, we can listen better, we can become better partners, but there is no one in the world who is worth pretending we are something that we are not.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
yesterday i experienced one of those 'only in new york' musical experiences.  they don't  happen as often anymore,  mainly because i don't go out as much.  the incredible meshell ndegeocello performed for the closing of the james baldwin exhibit at the david zwirner gallery. 
in collaboration with hilton als, staceyann chin, and a few other incredible artists,  they gave us an unforgettable,  unique, intimate powerfully-moving experience on race,  religion,  gender, the metoo movement and life.  to the 100 or so other souls in attendance - much love to you all. (and diane wiest was on my left!)
#officialmeshell #ricardorivera #metoo #jamesbaldwin #race #poetry #checkthekids #moments #nyc #art #csgrau #ricardodrivera

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
according to the times, cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan, a russian-american academic. kogan, who told facebook he was conducting academic research, built a facebook personality quiz app called "thisisyourdigitalife." when users downloaded the app, it scraped all of their available facebook data, including their friends, their likes and where they lived.

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer". in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field." despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytica until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

text:
john legend explains to bill maher why he spoke up about r. kelly, talks #metoo in music industry
#
john legend says he decided to speak out about r. kelly to give a voice to the "powerless" victims. while appearing on "real time with bill maher" friday night, the singer and late-night host discussed the #metoo movement in the music industry and texplosive documentary series "surviving r. kelly," where many women shared their stories of alleged sexual abuse and underage sex with the controversial r&b singer. "i think a lot of people have asked in the last few years, like, 'when is the #metoo movement going to come to the music industry?'" maher began. "i think what a lot of people are thinking is 'god that's so ubiquitous in the music industry, where would you even start?'" "yeah, i don't know," legend replied. "i mean i think clearly we're having this conversation about r.kelly, there's another article this week in the new york times about another musician and so i think there's a conversation being had. i just think music is probably a bit more decentralized." that other case was ryan adams, which you can read about here. when it comes to r. kelly, legend was one of the biggest stars featured in the lifetime documentary. the "all of…

text:
major moment: if you are a longtime supporter of @blackpress_radio you know we cover everything home game for the #knicks for the past decade. in fact the knicks have been the official nba team of blackpressradio for a decade.

many have asked why there hasn't been regular coverage this season. the easiest way to answer is to say #metoo

i have been experiencing extreme retaliation for coming forward and discussing my experiences with being #sexuallyassaulted by an nba player, enduring sexual harassment, discrimination in the nba. it became unbelievably difficult to contend with the #rapeculture of the nba. i have decided to get back to work while the lawyers handle the rest.

minutes ago, i met #cynthiamarshall the new interim ceo of the #dallasmavericks as she was on a lunchtime panel here at the event. as the final question, i was handed the mic and i asked her what the nba and #mavericks plan is for protecting female sports writers like me from #sexualassault #harassment #rapeculture in the nba. her reply is available on @blackpress_radio stories now - dc livers aka the fly on every wall 
#lebronjames #teamlebeon #teamgiannis #allstarweekend

major moment: if you are a longtime supporter of @blackpress_radio you know we cover everything home game for the #knicks for the past decade. in fact the knicks have been the official nba team of blackpressradio for a decade.

many have asked why there hasn't been regular coverage this season. the easiest way to answer is to say #metoo

i have been experiencing extreme retaliation for coming forward and discussing my experiences with being #sexuallyassaulted by an nba player, enduring sexual harassment, discrimination in the nba. it became unbelievably difficult to contend with the #rapeculture of the nba. i have decided to get back to work while the lawyers handle the rest.

minutes ago, i met #cynthiamarshall the new interim ceo of the #dallasmavericks as she was on a lunchtime panel here at the event. as the final question, i was handed the mic and i asked her what the nba and #mavericks plan is for protecting female sports writers like me from #sexualassault #harassment #rapeculture in the nba. her reply is available on @blackpress_radio stories now - dc livers aka the fly on every wall 
#lebronjames #teamlebeon #teamgiannis #allstarweekend

text:
gracias al @emac.fest por darme la oportunidad de seguir pisando fuerte, aunque sea con unos botines de 29,99 de plástico, del mango. 
quiero agradecer a todas las mujeres,adolescentes y niñas que vinieron al💫taller de ilustración feminista💕. cuando contamos nuestras vivencias en alto nos sentimos menos solas. la espiral del silencio nos ha consumido durante muchos años. no tengáis miedo, lo importante es darse cuenta, no castigarse por ello.💜
.
recordad que “la época te ayuda a entender el contexto pero no a justificar el machismo”. nuestra lucha es diaria y solo somos un grano más en la montaña que ya comenzaron a crear mujeres y hombres feministas hace muchos años, sobre todo mujeres. mi gran referente, simón beauvoir (la rosalía de 1949).
.
ahora nos toca a nosotras, tenemos que seguir aportando ese granito de arena para que generaciones futuras no permitan el acoso y micromachismos que hemos vivido y permitido nosotras. voy a ser tía por primera vez y de una niña, este tema me preocupa ahora aún más.
.
.
gracias a todas, no temáis.
.
.
#emacfest #burriana #feminismo  #feminist #taller #girlpower #nometoquesloscopys #ilustracion #💪🏻 #metoo

🌹sexual trauma is a big topic these day with the #metoo movement and women taking their power back.

🌹herbs can help heal your body and spirit. you can use adaptogens and nervines to help support your nervous system. you also might need some additional allies like rose or yarrow to put boundaries around your energy bodies. you may need some herbs to balance out your hormones and reproductive system from the trauma as well. .
🌹herbs have been a miracle in my life to heal my own sexual trauma. .
🌹i envision our bodies getting healed from traumas, so we can take our power back and allow the healing of the mother earth and the feminine to continue. .
🌹if you have questions, please dm me privately. i am here to support you to your empowerment and wrapping you up in rose flower essence and love.
.
.

text: for brunch today we have a buffalo chicken wrap and a side of something really spicy: #rafe by @rebekahweatherspoon, my first romance read, ever! i have soooo many friends who love romance but it always seemed a little silly to me...then i saw rafe, the buff male nanny. this is honestly the first time i’ve seen a guy on the cover of a romance novel and thought “whoa, yeah, okay.” i’m having so much fun reading this, and i am really surprised by how much i love the dynamic between rafe and dr. sloan. another thing i love about this book is that it’s very timely: i’ve already seen mentions of the racial divide in the country right now and the beginnings of the #metoo movement. basically, it’s a romance for modern ladies and i am here for it (and, you know, the muscular, tattoo-covered, motorcycle-riding rafe). do you guys read romance? give me recommendations below!

text:
僕の知り合いがバイト先の先輩達と飲んだ際に、他の人がトイレで席を空けた時、彼氏と別れたからヤらせてくれると思って来たけど、ヤらせてくれないなら帰るねと言って実際先に帰ったそうです。
また、#細川展裕 というプロデューサーと食事をした際、自宅に連れていかれ、話をした後帰る際に抱きつかれお尻を触られたそうです。目撃者もいます。
僕の知り合いは大丈夫でした。でも、それで次に苦しむ人、今も苦しんでいる人のことを考えたら居ても立っても居られませんでした。
#株式会社 #ヴィレッヂ #古田新太 #宮藤官九郎 #鴻上尚史 #metoo #劇団新感線 #第三舞台 #演劇 #セクハラ 
みんなセクハラに遭った人を実名告白してください。弱い立場の女性たちに漬け込んで平気で自らの欲望を満たそうとする。そんなこともうやめにしませんか。怖いかもしれません。みんな立ち上がりませんか。協力お願いします。
when my ex-girlfriend went to drink with seniors part time job, one said he came because you would sex with him because she had broken up with me. he continued saying he would go back home because he thought he couldn't sex with her ,and actually he did, went home.
another story.. she had a dinner with a producer ,named nobuhiro hosokawa. when she would go back home, he suddenly hugged and touched her hip. one witness.
my ex was ok. but think about next victim, still victim. i never be able to forgive. please stand up again for #metoo #sexual #harassment

text:
what is being a woman to you? 
how much of being a woman lies in physicality? 
is being a woman not also a self; a soul; a force? mother nature is not a mother for her breasts, but for her essence and power. 
you are no less a powerful, beautiful woman if you have no uterus, no period, no mammaries. 
what is being a woman to you?

text:
bebê de neo 🏥
.
aprende a ler sua filha por números e códigos de aparelhos.
não troca a fralda do próprio bebê.
conhece equipes médicas completas e sabe a hora do plantão de cada uma.
precisa entender que seu peito produz “mamá delivery”.
aguenta a dor de pontos da cesária , mas não suportar não poder pegar seu filho no colo.
é chamada de "mamãe" várias vezes por dias por pessoas vestidas de branco.
não pode tomar decisões pelo sua filha, pois no fundo, nem sabe ao certo o que está acontecendo com ela.
mãe de neo é comprar o enxoval com o maior carinho e ver a filha toda hora sem roupa.
é ver o bebê mamar sentado no copinho depois da sonda de alimentação limpa!
é nunca querer ir pra casa sem o bebê.
é chorar horas a fio.
é não conseguir terminar de escrever cada vez que lembra.
as lágrimas rolam de gratidão.
tudo isso acabou!
ela enfim está em casa. .

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."
dailyhunt

on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
“um ser humano é uma parte do todo chamado por nós universo, uma parte limitada no tempo e no espaço. ele experimenta a si mesmo, seus pensamentos e sentimentos como algo separado do resto, uma espécie de ilusão ótica de sua consciência. essa ilusão é uma espécie de prisão para nós, restringindo-nos aos nossos desejos pessoais e ao afeto por algumas pessoas mais próximas de nós. nossa tarefa deve ser libertar-nos dessa prisão ampliando nosso círculo de compaixão para abraçar todas as criaturas vivas e toda a natureza em sua beleza ”. - albert einsten

text:
"it's going to take all of us" 
this parody pretty much sums of the collective scrutiny women [unfairly] face when they come forward with their truths about abuse and harassment. it's time to #believewomen and to respect victims of sexual assault. but we can't just stop at believing women; it's not enough. we need to stop this culture of innate subjection and objectification of women as solely sexual beings that men are entitled to do almost anything they want with and say almost anything they want to. men should also be leaders of the #metoo movement - we can make a difference simply by not tolerating private conversations or "locker room talk" that demean. #itsgoingtotakeallofus

text:
i tend to say that there were two sides to my sexual assault within the church. on one hand, i have struggled with the actual, physical act of abuse itself. on the other hand, my family and i suffered an abuse of its own kind at the hands of an entire church congregation. we were blamed, humiliated, and betrayed by some of our closest friends. people that we had known, loved, and considered family turned their backs on us, ostracized us, and terminated their relationships with us altogether - because i told my truth and pressed charges against my abuser. while i have struggled with this betrayal for the better part of a decade, i’ve  held tightly to this quote. many people spoke out against us, persecuted my family, blamed me, and sung my abuser’s praises - most remained silent. they did not utter a word. they did not take sides. and to me, honestly, that’s always been worse, in a way. when we don’t take sides, or speak up for the oppressed, it gives abusers the space & power to thrive. all that evil needs to succeed is the silence of the bystander. 🌻
•
•
•
•
•

text:
but wylie wasn’t just talking about fashion. he had recently been exposed to a new discipline: “information operations”, which ranks alongside land, sea, air and space in the us military’s doctrine of the “five-dimensional battle space”. his brief ranged across the scl group – the british government has paid scl to conduct counter-extremism operations in the middle east, and the us department of defense has contracted it to work in afghanistan.

i tell him that another former employee described the firm as “mi6 for hire”, and i’d never quite understood it.
.
- it’s like dirty mi6 because you’re not constrained. there’s no having to go to a judge to apply for permission. it’s normal for a ‘market research company’ to amass data on domestic populations. and if you’re working in some country and there’s an auxiliary benefit to a current client with aligned interests, well that’s just a bonus.
.
when i ask how bannon even found scl, wylie tells me what sounds like a tall tale, though it’s one he can back up with an email about how mark block, a veteran republican strategist, happened to sit next to a cyberwarfare expert for the us air force on a plane. - and the cyberwarfare guy is like, ‘oh, you should meet scl. they do cyberwarfare for elections.’
.
it was bannon who took this idea to the mercers: robert mercer – the co-ceo of the hedge fund renaissance technologies, who used his billions to pursue a rightwing agenda, donating to republican causes and supporting republican candidates – and his daughter rebekah.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
but wylie wasn’t just talking about fashion. he had recently been exposed to a new discipline: “information operations”, which ranks alongside land, sea, air and space in the us military’s doctrine of the “five-dimensional battle space”. his brief ranged across the scl group – the british government has paid scl to conduct counter-extremism operations in the middle east, and the us department of defense has contracted it to work in afghanistan.

i tell him that another former employee described the firm as “mi6 for hire”, and i’d never quite understood it.
.
- it’s like dirty mi6 because you’re not constrained. there’s no having to go to a judge to apply for permission. it’s normal for a ‘market research company’ to amass data on domestic populations. and if you’re working in some country and there’s an auxiliary benefit to a current client with aligned interests, well that’s just a bonus.
.
when i ask how bannon even found scl, wylie tells me what sounds like a tall tale, though it’s one he can back up with an email about how mark block, a veteran republican strategist, happened to sit next to a cyberwarfare expert for the us air force on a plane. - and the cyberwarfare guy is like, ‘oh, you should meet scl. they do cyberwarfare for elections.’
.
it was bannon who took this idea to the mercers: robert mercer – the co-ceo of the hedge fund renaissance technologies, who used his billions to pursue a rightwing agenda, donating to republican causes and supporting republican candidates – and his daughter rebekah.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
قیمت #پراید۱۱۱ به پنجاه ملیون نزدیک شد آین در نوع خودش شاهکاره البته فروش با آین مبلغ . این باز بر می گرده به نجابت و حیا و خوب بودن مردم ما که البته داره تبدیل به یه چیز دیگه میشه مقاله زیر را بخوانید از خودم هست :؛
🔴 سناريویی برای بازار خودرو !
▪️در اين روزها بازار خودرو داغ داغ شده است، بطوری كه پرايد در چند قدمی پنجاه ميليون تومان ميباشد. سوال اينجاست كه آيا دلال ها توانستند قيمت خودرو ها را انقدر بالا بكشند؟؟
جواب: خیر
▪️دلال يا نمايشگاه دار اصلا توان اين كار را ندارد و نخواهد داشت و تنها دليل افزايش نرخ بدست خود كارخانه ها ميباشد. 
جالب اينجاست كه اين روزها من را ياد روزهایی كه دلار از چهارده هزار بطور شارپی رفت برای بیست هزار تومان انداخت، آيا رشد قيمت ارز بدست دلال و صراف بود؟؟ و بعد از افزايش نرخ ارز چه اتفاقی افتاد؟؟
▪️كاری به سر كسانی كه سرمايه هایشان را در صف خريد ارز به باد دادند آمد كه اگر دلار به هفت هزار تومان هم برسد ديگر طرف بیزینس ارزی نخواهند رفت. به اصطلاح نقره داغ شدند ▪️حال نوبت بازار خودرو است 
همان سناريو دوباره تكرار و اينبار در جهت خودرو قرار گرفته است. 
كسانی كه پژو پارس را امروز صد ميليون خريداری كردند و پرايد را چهل هشت ميليونی كسانی هستند كه در روزهای آينده مهر نقره داغ بر پيشانی شان برجسته خواهد شد.
▪️چطور؟ صنعت خودرو در طول بيش از دو سال با زيان انباشته مواجه شده بود. بيشتر بخاطر نرخ گذاری ها و سياست هاي غلط. حال اينبار نه تنها با فروش چشم گير خودروها بصورت فوري با احتساب پنج درصد كمتر از قيمت بازار زيان گذشته شركت را به سود تبديل خواهد كرد و همچنين انجام تعهد خود را به دولت اجرایی ميكند و همچنين با عرضه خودرو به بازار حباب ايجاد شده در قيمت ها را تخليه خواهد كرد. و پولی كه اين مدت دلال ها به جيب زدند رو به چرخه شركت باز ميگردانند.
▪️گويا شركت سايپا با اعلام فروش فوری اولين قدم را برای پس فردا برداشته است.
جالب اینجاست کمسیون تلفیق و برنامه اجازه واردات هزار ششصد دستگاه خودرو وارداتی به دولت داده یعنی دولت سود خودش در شب عید گرفت پس این تغییر قیمت از کجاست

stop_filter_tweet: قیمت به پنجاه ملیون نزدیک شد آین در نوع خودش شاهکاره البته فروش با آین مبلغ . این باز بر می گرده به نجابت و حیا و خوب بودن مردم ما که البته داره تبدیل به یه چیز دیگه میشه مقاله زیر را بخوانید از خودم هست : ؛ 🔴 سناريویی برای بازار خودرو ! ▪️در اين روزها بازار خودرو داغ داغ شده است، بطوری كه پرايد در چند قدمی پنجاه ميليون تومان ميباشد . سوال اينجاست كه آيا دلال ها توانستند قيمت خودرو ها را انقدر بالا بكشند؟؟ جواب : خیر ▪️دلال يا نمايشگاه دار اصلا توان اين كار را ندارد و نخواهد داشت و تنها دليل افزايش نرخ بدست خود كارخانه ها ميباشد . جالب اينجاست كه اين روزها من را ياد روزهایی كه دلار از چهارده هزار بطور شارپی رفت برای بیست هزار تومان انداخت، آيا رشد قيمت ارز بدست دلال و صراف بود؟؟ و بعد از افزايش نرخ ارز چه اتفاقی افتاد؟؟ ▪️كاری به سر كسانی كه سرمايه هایشان را در صف خريد ارز به باد دادند آمد كه اگر دلار به هفت هزار تومان هم برسد ديگر طرف بیزینس ارزی نخواهند رفت . به اصطلاح نقره داغ شدند ▪️حال نوبت بازار خودرو است همان سناريو دوباره تكرار و اينبار در جهت خودرو قرار گرفته است . كسانی كه پژو پارس را امروز صد ميليون خريداری كردند و پرايد را چهل هشت ميليونی كسانی هستند كه در روزهای آينده مهر نقره داغ بر پيشانی شان برجسته خواهد شد . ▪️چطور؟ صنعت خودرو در طول بيش از دو سال با زيان انباشته مواجه شده بود . بيشتر بخاطر نرخ گذاری ها و سياست هاي غلط . حال اينبار نه تنها با فروش چشم گير خودروها بصورت فوري با احتساب پنج درصد كمتر از قيمت بازار زيان گذشته شركت را به سود تبديل خواهد كرد و همچنين انجام تعهد خود را به دولت اجرایی ميكند و همچنين با عرضه خودرو به بازار حباب ايجاد شده در قيمت ها را تخليه خواهد كرد . و پولی كه اين مدت دلال ها به جيب زدند رو به چرخه شركت باز ميگردانند . ▪️گويا شركت سايپا با اعلام فروش فوری اولين قدم را برای پس فردا برداشته است . جالب اینجاست کمسیون تلفیق و برنامه اجازه واردات هزار ششصد دستگاه خودرو وارداتی به دولت داده یعنی دولت سود خودش در شب عید گرفت پس این تغییر قیمت از کجاست یران_تسلیتایپاراید۱۱۱

text: ett år har gått sedan vi marscherade tillsammas i strömstad i samband med #metoo. idag stod vi återigen enade för att visa att vi fortfarande kämpar för en jämställd värld där pojkar och flickor ges samma möjligheter✊. föreläsning, fackeltåg, middag och bio stod på agendan idag, som en del av #winterwordfestival. dagen anordnades bland annat av gruppen "kvinnor på tvärs från partierna i strömstad" där vår karla representerar miljöpartiet. håll utkik efter fler happenings under våren, då vi uppmärksammar att det är 100 år sedan beslutet togs om allmän rösträtt för kvinnor!💪🎉 #lokalpolitik #strömstad #metoo #wedo #miljöpartiet #mpströmstad #mp

text:
where would you rather do vineyard work? beaujolais (gamay) or the northern rhône (syrah)?
👇🏼no wrong answers👇🏼
-
pictured above is beaujolais and the northern rhône is over at @viticolewine. 2 places i spent a few hours in the vines on my latest viticole trip.
-
it’s a tough call between the two. both will make you cry uncle in their own diabolical way. for my 2 cents head over to @viticolewine, but before you do, what’ll it be? the flatter slopes of fleurie or the treacherous hillsides of saint joseph?

name: Brian McClintic MS
tweet_full:
where would you rather do vineyard work? beaujolais (gamay) or the northern rhône (syrah)?
👇🏼no wrong answers👇🏼
-
pictured above is beaujolais and the northern rhône is over at @viticolewine. 2 places i spent a few hours in the vines on my latest viticole trip.
-
it’s a tough call between the two. both will make you cry uncle in their own diabolical way. for my 2 cents head over to @viticolewine, but before you do, what’ll it be? the flatter slopes of fleurie or the treacherous hillsides of saint joseph?
